column48: It would not have surprised me if any/all of those events had occurred simply because we are rarely made aware of the whole story.  Unless one is involved firsthand with a situation, it is difficult to know what is true and what isn't based on what is reported.  Politicians of all parties (and many business people) will sometimes do whatever it takes to get something accomplished that is of their own interest.  This is not always a bad thing or affects the average person, but I think it's naive to assume it doesn't happen.
